article.headline: W. Michigan 85, Buffalo 70
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Martell McLemore scored 24 points and David Kool added 23 to help Western Michigan defeat Buffalo 85-70 on Monday night. The Broncos (12-9, 4-4 Mid-American Conference) shot 58.5 percent from the field (31 of 53), including 11-for-22 from 3-point range. Donald Lawson added 11 points and Mike Douglas had a career-high 10 assists for the Broncos, who snapped a two-game losing streak. Western Michigan led 14-12 early, and went on a 9-2 run to take a 23-14 lead on Donald Lawson's jumper with 8:41 to go in the first half. McLemore gave the Broncos their biggest lead, 73-51, on a jumper with 8:18 to go. Western Michigan led the entire way, and outrebounded Buffalo 32-29. Rodney Pierce paced the Bulls (11-8, 4-4) with 29 points and Calvin Betts had a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds.
